1. What information do we collect
We collect your information in three ways, more detail is provided
        below:
a.
Information you provide (either directly or through a third
        party)
·
If you choose to bind your phone number with your
DramaBite
account, you may need to provide us with your phone number,
        password and SMS verification code, which only your option and not
        mandatory. These will be bound to your
DramaBite
account, for the purpose of enabling login by phone number.
·
Profile Information. We collect information that you provide when
        you want to enrich your profile information, such as your date of birth,
        gender, height, weight, occupation, location, nationality. These pieces
        of information are not mandatory; you may choose whether or not to
        provide them. You can also change your nickname and avatar
.
·
User content, including comments, pictures, text and voice messages,
        photographs, videos, and virtual item videos that you choose to upload
        or broadcast on our Services.
·
Transaction information. In order to purchase offerings provided as
        part of our Services, you can get then by paying us, we will collect
        your transaction information (such as purchase date, items, etc.) so
        that you can check your transaction records while protecting your
        property to the maximum extent.
Please note that we do not obtain and collect your payment account
          number, bank information (such as bank name, account, etc.) and
          security code
,
these information will be collected by the third party payment
          channel (Apple or Google).
To ensure a secure payment environment, we may require you to
        provide some information such as your name, phone number and email when
        you pay.
·
Feedback information. Any information that you provide in communication
        with us, when you seek our technical or user services support, exercise
        your right as the information subject.
b.
Information we collect when you use our Services
We may collect certain information when you are using our Services. The
        type of information that we collect may vary, but generally
        include:
·
Device information. We collect information from and about the devices
        you use. For example, we collect information about your hardware and
        software, such as the application version, devices memory, device ID,
        IDFA, GAID, device model, etc..
·
User behavior information. We collect information about your activity
        through our Services. For example, we may collect information about how
        you interact with
us
, how you communicate with other users
,
following list, browsing history, the time/frequency/duration of
        your activities, and your use records and actions.
·
Location Information. We will infer your approximate location based on
        your IP address and SIM card information. We will not collect your
        precise geographical location information (such as GPS).
c.
information we collect from third parties
When you register our Services, those information we import from your
        connected social media account (such as Apple ID, Google)
in order to set up your profile, including your nickname as it appears
        on your social media profile, your user ID and your avatar. We use this
        information to create your account for providing the Services in
        accordance with your request.
We may collect information about you from other users or third parties
        or other external sources. For example, if another user uploads or
        shares your information or you access our Services through a third-party
        application. We may also collect some information when you use or
        interact with third-party services that may be available on our
        Services, such as share buttons. However, please note that this Policy
        does not and will not extend, which shall be subject to the respective
        third-party’s privacy policies.
